		<p>Great interview! I agree with the sentiments of NiGHTS shouldn&#8217;t have a sequel. It was such a complete game to begin with. It would have been best to have a Wii port rather than a new game in my opinion. Journey of Dreams was a great game, but I wish that it didn&#8217;t have the NiGHTS name, and instead have all new characters. That way, I think it would have been much better received. I hope that the PC version is found and ported to the new consoles. I it isn&#8217;t the Saturn version running emulated as suggested in another post, because there are a lot of things in the Saturn version that could be polished &#8211; FMV, draw distance, distant objects fading in from baackground, mesh transparencies, model complexity, lighting effects, and ity would have been nice to have an online leaderboard of scores and replays I reckon, a christmas/holiday mode for the whole game + presents that can be be added to by Sega, including things like running Sonic around the levels. I thought they were great, and would be awesome to be available to owners of new consoles (or even a dreamcast version would be both crazy and awesome!)</p>

